GitHub Copilot is an AI-powered coding assistant that acts like a “pair programmer,” helping developers write code faster, reduce repetitive tasks, and focus more on problem-solving.


Key Features of GitHub Copilot
Code suggestions: Autocompletes functions, boilerplate, and repetitive code as you type in your IDE.

Code explanations: Explains unfamiliar code snippets or libraries in plain language.

Pull request support: Generates descriptions of changes, reviews code, and suggests improvements.

Terminal integration: Executes commands and builds workflows using natural language in the CLI.

Copilot Chat: Lets you ask questions about your code, debug issues, or get step-by-step guidance.

Copilot Spaces: Organizes project context so Copilot provides more relevant answers.


Limitations & Considerations
Accuracy: Suggestions may not always be optimal or secure; developers must review code carefully.

Licensing concerns: Generated code may resemble open-source snippets, so teams should check compliance.

Cost: Free tier is limited; advanced features require paid plans.

Privacy: Enterprise users should configure governance to prevent unauthorized access. 
